cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about improving the accuracy of deep convolutional neural networks for visual recognition. The paper specifically focuses on a new pooling strategy called "spatial pyramid pooling" to eliminate the fixed-size requirement of input images. This work is most likely to be categorized under computer vision (cs.CV) as it deals with image classification. It could also be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves improving the accuracy of neural networks. Additionally, it could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves developing more principled strategies for image recognition. Neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM) are also possible categories as they are related to the use of deep learning for image recognition.
